<title>POLAND: KPW clears PLI rights for public trade.</title>
<headline>KPW clears PLI rights for public trade.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-06-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Polish Securities Commission (KPW) has cleared for public trade the planned rights issue by wholesaler and retailer Polish Life Improvement (PLI) SA, the KPW said in a statement on Thursday.</p>
<p> Tranches		  No Of Shares	   Subscription</p>
<p>			     Offered		  Period</p>
<p> 1-for-2 rights	  3,525,607		Aug 11-Sept 1*</p>
<p> Record date:	    August 1</p>
<p> Lead Manager:	   Bank Handlowy SA brokerage</p>
<p> Use Of Proceeds:	To help open six supermarkets in 1998</p>
<p>*NOTE: A second subscription period from September 11 to October 2 will take place if not all shares are subscribed to in the first phase. If shares remain then, an open tranche will take place from October 24 to 28.</p>
<p>No. of existing shares: 7,051,213</p>
<p>-- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
